==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tetramerous
<hw>Te*tram"er*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Tetra-</ets> + Gr. <?/ part.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having the parts arranged in sets of four;
<as>as, a <ex>tetramerous</ex> flower</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having four joints in each of the
tarsi; -- said of certain insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tetrameter</ent>⟦br⟧
